      "uri": "at://did:plc:7f3qpp3nf2n5lzp2xsnv5yf7/app.bsky.feed.post/3mqju4gbd2k2b",
      "likeCount": 0
    },
    {
      "thumb": "https://cdn.bsky.app/img/feed_thumbnail/plain/did:plc:hu35oubkccqrxl4ldgczpgw7/bafkreieveoup2v4t74ftu2rcmzzysmchcklrul5bo3frscfe2ej3vfbooi",
      "fullsize": "https://cdn.bsky.app/img/feed_fullsize/plain/did:plc:hu35oubkccqrxl4ldgczpgw7/bafkreieveoup2v4t74ftu2rcmzzysmchcklrul5bo3frscfe2ej3vfbooi",
      "alt": "If we assume for the sake of exploration that this chiasmic structure is metaphysically true - that this is a pattern baked into the ontology of any species that lives long enough to create Al - then what does that imply about the world to come?\nTo put less strain on you to predict the future, to invite you instead to explore the space, use two axes to guide you dystopic/utopic, and anthropocentric/holistic. We either end in a new Eden, or become trapped in a dark mirror of the ancient one; we are either gods over Al (or Al are gods over us, but that one's played out) or we are co-equals in the universe.",
      "ratio": 0.7939,
